In order to receive a free ticket to the event (unless they are willing to pay for a VIP ticket), spectators had to pay for a number of tasks or "actions", such as volunteering, sending e-mails to world leaders, making phone calls or other significant things that help raise awareness of the goal of eliminating global poverty.
But what success did the Global Citizen Festival have when it was just 12 years away to achieve its goal?
