According to Global Citizen, since 2011 there have been more than 19 million "actions" from its supporters, which have promoted different objectives.
The organisation says these actions have driven world leaders to announce commitments and policies worth more than $37 billion, which will affect the lives of more than 2.25 billion people by 2030.
