The group also said that after more than 5,000 actions were carried out in Britain to improve the nutrition of mothers and children, the government announced that it would finance the project The Power of Nutrition, which would provide nutrition interventions for 5 million women and children.
The answer to one of the most common questions on their website: "What makes you think you can eliminate extreme poverty?"
Global Citizen replied: “It will be a long and difficult road, sometimes we will fall and fail.
But like the great civil rights or anti-aparheid movements that took place before us, we will succeed, because together we are stronger.
