2004: on December 26, a severe earthquake on the west coast of the Indonesian province of Aceh, in northern Sumatra, triggered a tsunami that hit 14 countries, causing the deaths of 226,000 people on the coast of the Indian Ocean, more than half of whom were from Aceh.
